## Portfolio Project

**Suspension Corner Assembly**  
A static double-wishbone suspension corner (lower A-arm, upper A-arm, upright, hub, brake disc) built as the centrepiece CAD portfolio piece for SAE Thapar application.

| Component | Status |
|-----------|--------|
| Anatomy research & briefing | ✅ |
| Wishbone (upper + lower A-arms) | ✅ |
| Upright + Hub | ✅ |
| Brake Disc | ✅ |
| Full Assembly | ✅ |

Folder: `cad/portfolio/suspension-corner/`  
Scope: static assembly (correct trapezoid geometry, camber-gain principle demonstrated). Full kinematics/roll-centre simulation deferred until Team Fateh mentorship + reference car are available.  
Completed: July 2026 (rebuilt after a first attempt had incorrect A-arm-to-upright anatomy)

---

## How to open these files

1. Download the `.f3d` file
2. Open Fusion 360 → File → Open → Upload from my computer
3. Select the downloaded file

